==English==
===Noun===
'''outrage'''
# an [[extremely]] [[violent]] or [[vicious]] [[attack]]; an [[atrocity]]
# an [[offensive]], [[immoral]] or [[indecent]] act
# the [[resentful]] [[anger]] caused by such acts
# (Obsolete usage) destructive [[rampage]] as e.g. "by the outrage and fury of the river [[wiki:Effra|Effra]]" in sn old description of [[wiki:flood|flood]] damage. 

===Transitive Verb===
'''to outrage'''
# to commit an outrage
# to cause [[resentment]] by such an act

